<main class="mx-auto w-full max-w-4xl px-6 py-10 print:px-0">
  <header class="flex flex-col gap-2">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-stone-500">Rules</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-stone-900">Roll The Dice</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-stone-600">
      A host-led trivia game built for in-room play.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="mt-6 rounded-3xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm print:border-none print:bg-transparent print:p-0 print:shadow-none">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Quick Start</h2>
    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-sm text-stone-700">
      <li>Host sets the number of questions per rep and assigns reps for the round.</li>
      <li>Rep rolls for topic and difficulty, then the host assigns a question.</li>
      <li>Correct answers score points; incorrect answers open a steal.</li>
      <li>Any team can buzz to steal; host decides the first buzzer.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 print:grid-cols-1">
    <div class="rounded-3xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm print:border-none print:bg-transparent print:shadow-none">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Setup</h2>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-sm text-stone-700">
        <li>Teams have any number of players.</li>
        <li>The host assigns one representative per team each round.</li>
        <li>
          Questions per rep:
          <strong class="text-stone-900">
            <%= @game ? (@game.settings["questions_per_rep"].presence || 3) : "set by host (default 3)" %>
          </strong>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-3xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm print:border-none print:bg-transparent print:shadow-none">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Topics</h2>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-sm text-stone-700">
        <li>General Knowledge</li>
        <li>History</li>
        <li>Sports</li>
        <li>Science</li>
        <li>Entertainment</li>
        <li>Geography</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-6 rounded-3xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm print:border-none print:bg-transparent print:shadow-none">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Per-Question Flow</h2>
    <ol class="mt-3 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-6 text-sm text-stone-700">
      <li>Roll dice for topic and enter the result.</li>
      <li>Roll dice for difficulty and enter the result.</li>
      <li>If chaos is enabled, resolve the chaos roll.</li>
      <li>Choose a lifeline (optional).</li>
      <li>Answer and score the question.</li>
      <li>If incorrect, open a steal and award points if the steal is correct.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 print:grid-cols-1">
    <div class="rounded-3xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm print:border-none print:bg-transparent print:shadow-none">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Difficulty + Points</h2>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-sm text-stone-700">
        <li>Easy (1-2): 2 points</li>
        <li>Medium (3-4): 4 points</li>
        <li>Hard (5-6): 5 points</li>
        <li>Multiplier: ×2 (correct gains, incorrect loses)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-3xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm print:border-none print:bg-transparent print:shadow-none">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Chaos Roll</h2>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-sm text-stone-700">
        <li>1-2: host chooses another team to answer.</li>
        <li>3-4: target team rolls difficulty; if lower, swap.</li>
        <li>5-6: rep chooses double points or double penalty.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 print:grid-cols-1">
    <div class="rounded-3xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm print:border-none print:bg-transparent print:shadow-none">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Lifelines</h2>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-sm text-stone-700">
        <li>Single teammate: must be someone you do not know (host verifies).</li>
        <li>Whole team: consumes all remaining lifelines for that team.</li>
        <li>Whole team must deliberate out loud.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-3xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm print:border-none print:bg-transparent print:shadow-none">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Steal Rules</h2>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-sm text-stone-700">
        <li>Any team can buzz in after an incorrect answer.</li>
        <li>Host chooses who buzzed first.</li>
        <li>If correct, the stealing team gains the points.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-6 rounded-3xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm print:border-none print:bg-transparent print:shadow-none">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Examples</h2>
    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-sm text-stone-700">
      <li>Topic roll 2 → History; difficulty roll 5 → Hard (5 points).</li>
      <li>Rep uses ×2 multiplier → correct = +10, incorrect = −10.</li>
      <li>Chaos roll 3 → target team rolls 2 (easy), swap occurs.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <div class="mt-8 flex justify-between text-xs text-stone-500 print:hidden">
    <a href="/" class="underline">Back to home</a>
    <button onclick="window.print()" class="underline">Print rules</button>
  </div>
</main>
